				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">This is what came from the FV server boards on this matter:
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Whether or not the issue of the banker who was not tied in and would exchange plat was real or a diversion, there is another bug. 
<br />

<br />
I am posting a copy of this on the TCH forum soley because I believe that the more public such information is and the more people feebacka dn petition the faster it will get fixed. The issue is this - and it can be done at any merchant that sells the right smithing supplies.
<br />

<br />
Quoted from a FV forum 
<br />
pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...=1&stop=20
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Quote:
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
We figured out the plat bug.
<br />
Traiya managed to interrupt the bot and gum up his combines, and got a look at what was in the forge. We played around with the possible combines, checking prices, and found the culprit behind the plat dupe bug.
<br />
3 small bricks of medium quality ore + 1 flask of water = 1 large brick of medium quality ore. Alternatively: 12 silver + 1 silver = 6 plat. It's a 5000% profit margin. A bot macrod at a rate of 26 combines per minute (8 10 slot bags) will make 9600 platinum per hour. This is what has devalued platinum. The post about a hidden banker in befallen was just a diversion. If people stopped looking for the bug, then it would buy them time until they noticed the problem was still worsening. We have reported and bugged this, and hopefully this ends the dupe bug.
<br />

<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
To solve the bot problem, petition, feedback and report such people as you see macroing. They may warp back and forth between forges and vendors. If you wish to interrupt them you can stop this by casting mass mod rod, putting an item in the forge to screw up their combines or aggroing / killing the merchant. 
<br />

<br />
In addition please /feedback and /bug the mis pricing on the merchants, perhaps send complaint e-mails also. According to EQ traders the price should be 2pp and change per not 1s for the small blocks so somewhere, some time this got changed.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This is the actual FV thread:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=4585.topic&start=1&stop=20" target="_blank">http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=4585.topic&start=1&stop=20</a>
<br />

<br />
I think it sucks really. I have been shopping for mid end items and have had no luck finding them, then I decide to go a little higher and was looking at a Staff of Flowing Waters for my BL twink and some asspuppet wants 220k for it, one week ago it is 60-85k. That is the kind of shit that is major annoying![/quote]<span class="gensmall"></span>


				</div></td>
			</tr>
